'''William Ross Johnston''' is a historian in [[Queensland]], Australia. In 2012, he was awarded the John Douglas Kerr Medal of Distinction for his rigour in his teaching and research of [[History of Queensland|Queensland's history]].<ref>{{Cite web|url=http://qldhistorians.org.au/citation-for-the-2012-winner-of-the-john-douglas-kerr-medal-of-distinction-ross-johnston/|title=CITATION FOR THE 2012 WINNER OF THE JOHN DOUGLAS KERR MEDAL OF DISTINCTION: ROSS JOHNSTON|last=Hopkins-Weise|first=Jeff|date=|website=Professional Historians Association (Queensland)|archive-url=|archive-date=|dead-url=|access-date=25 May 2017}}</ref>

